SIMPLE: mesotartaric
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mesotartaric
<hw>mes`o*tar*tar"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Meso-</ets> + <ets>tartaric</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, an acid called also
<altname>inactive tartaric acid</altname>. It is an optically inactive
stereoisomer of <isa>tartaric acid</isa> due to internal compensation of
the rotatory activity of the two asymmetric centers; it has a plane of
symmetry in the molecule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mesotheca</ent>⟦br⟧
